ri":"new-year-message-wwf-pandas-2019/","slug":"new-year-message-wwf-pandas-2019","date":"2019-01-09T15:42:26","content":"<p>WWF Pandas, that is. If you&#8217;re familiar with the work of our Pandas (yes, true to our iconic logo we call ourselves Pandas), you&#8217;d know that we protect the world&#8217;s precious resources and natural landscapes by sparking the change needed to do so. So if every Panda could have a wish for 2019, what would [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Janissa Ng","slug":"janissa-ng","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/878af2e67bd7d4b058ec3d614d76ab36?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"2019 wishlist","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/2019-wishlist/","slug":"2019-wishlist"},{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Earth Hour","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/earth-hour/","slug":"earth-hour"},{"name":"new year message","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/new-year-message/","slug":"new-year-message"},{"name":"PACT","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/pact/","slug":"pact"},{"name":"plastic reduction","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastic-reduction/","slug":"plastic-reduction"},{"name":"plastics in nature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastics-in-nature/","slug":"plastics-in-nature"},{"name":"saspo","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/saspo/","slug":"saspo"},{"name":"wildlife rangers","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/wildlife-rangers/","slug":"wildlife-rangers"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Personality feature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/personality-feature/","slug":"personality-feature"},{"name":"Wildlife","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/wildlife/","slug":"wildlife"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Small_WW1113726.jpg","altText":"new year message","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Small_WW1113726-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Small_WW1113726.jpg 1000w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDozNDM5","title":"COP24: Why We Should Stop Saying the Solution to Climate Change is Education","uri":"what-is-climate-change-cop24-katowice-education/","slug":"what-is-climate-change-cop24-katowice-education","date":"2018-12-21T12:43:31","content":"<p>The writer is Panda Ambassador at WWF-Singapore, Wesley Poh, who was covering news from COP24 (2-15 Dec) at Katowice, Poland. Here, Wesley sheds light on why climate change is not as simple and straight-forward as you think it is.  KATOWICE, Poland, 13 Dec 2018 —&nbsp; It is Education Day at COP24, and there are side [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":null,"slug":null,"avatar":null},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"cop24","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cop24/","slug":"cop24"},{"name":"environmental education","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/environmental-education/","slug":"environmental-education"},{"name":"katowice cop24 2018","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/katowice-cop24-2018/","slug":"katowice-cop24-2018"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-design-11.jpg","altText":"what is climate change","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-design-11-300x225.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-design-11.jpg 1000w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyNDU2","title":"WWF Insider: Saving the Great Whales","uri":"wwfinsider-in-1-minute-saving-the-great-whales/","slug":"wwfinsider-in-1-minute-saving-the-great-whales","date":"2018-10-04T18:26:48","content":"<p>A minute a day to save wildlife The next 1 minute will tell you if the world is doing enough for our wildlife. You probably don’t know this but every day this week, the fates of endangered wildlife will be decided. Here, our bite-sized pictorial updates about wildlife (ICYMI: check out our previous #WWFInsider in 1 Minute here) [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Janissa Ng","slug":"janissa-ng","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/878af2e67bd7d4b058ec3d614d76ab36?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"CITES standing committee","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cites-standing-committee/","slug":"cites-standing-committee"},{"name":"commercial whaling","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/commercial-whaling/","slug":"commercial-whaling"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"great whales","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/great-whales/","slug":"great-whales"},{"name":"japanese whaling","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/japanese-whaling/","slug":"japanese-whaling"},{"name":"sei whales","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/sei-whales/","slug":"sei-whales"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Small_WW22034.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Small_WW22034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Small_WW22034.jpg 1000w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyMTU1","title":"Earth Hour Challenge: Easy ways to halve your water usage","uri":"earth-hour-water-challenge/","slug":"earth-hour-water-challenge","date":"2017-03-22T19:21:45","content":"<p>Even as scarcity drives up water prices here, we are losing islands in the Pacific to rising water levels. With Earth Hour coming up, we challenged Wee Leng (who writes at earthleng.com) to find easy ways that ordinary Singaporeans can reduce our daily water usage. This Earth Hour, tell us what you will be doing [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Janissa Ng","slug":"janissa-ng","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/878af2e67bd7d4b058ec3d614d76ab36?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Earth Hour","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/earth-hour/","slug":"earth-hour"},{"name":"Singapore","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/singapore/","slug":"singapore"},{"name":"water","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/water/","slug":"water"},{"name":"water wastage","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/water-wastage/","slug":"water-wastage"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/59434-1.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/59434-1-300x196.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/59434-1-1024x670.jpg 1024w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyMTQw","title":"Unplug &#038; Unwind: 5 Uniquely Singaporean things to do during Earth Hour","uri":"5-uniquely-singaporean-things-to-do-during-earth-hour/","slug":"5-uniquely-singaporean-things-to-do-during-earth-hour","date":"2017-03-18T12:35:36","content":"<p>The lights go off, and the world switches on. Earth Hour, on 25 March this year, is not only a time for people to stand in solidarity with climate change, but also a time to celebrate the movement. We have compiled a list of things for you to do during the hour: from fun family [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Janissa Ng","slug":"janissa-ng","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/878af2e67bd7d4b058ec3d614d76ab36?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/230693.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/230693-300x199.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/230693-1024x679.jpg 1024w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyMTEw","title":"Singapore’s Budget 2017: How it impacts our environment","uri":"singapores-budget-2017-how-it-impacts-our-environment/","slug":"singapores-budget-2017-how-it-impacts-our-environment","date":"2017-02-22T15:29:35","content":"<p>Singapore’s recent Budget 2017 unveiled a few pro-sustainability measures. Delving into these measures, we’ve broken them down for you from a conservation perspective and evaluated how effective these measures are in protecting our environment. &nbsp; A FIRST STEP WITH CARBON TAX Singapore has become the first country in Southeast Asia to impose a carbon tax [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Sandeep Chamling Rai","slug":"scraiwwf-sg","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c783127d1f2e7b95e3c38f13fb9158eb?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"budget 2017","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/budget-2017/","slug":"budget-2017"},{"name":"carbon tax","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/carbon-tax/","slug":"carbon-tax"},{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"environment","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/environment/","slug":"environment"},{"name":"Paris Agreement","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/paris-agreement/","slug":"paris-agreement"},{"name":"Singapore","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/singapore/","slug":"singapore"},{"name":"water","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/water/","slug":"water"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/3059951.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/3059951-300x220.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/3059951-1024x750.jpg 1024w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyMDkz","title":"5 Things You Didn’t Know About Pangolins","uri":"5-things-you-didnt-know-about-pangolins/","slug":"5-things-you-didnt-know-about-pangolins","date":"2017-02-18T08:00:33","content":"<p>Pangolins are one of the shyest.. Wait, how much do you know about them? 1) Its name means “something that rolls up” &nbsp; Pangolins roll up into a ball when they are threatened. So, it is no surprise that the word “pangolin”, which originates from the Malay word &#8220;pengguling&#8221;, literally means “something that rolls up”! [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Veronica Fernandez","slug":"veronica-fernandez","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3805e3818bfa3c1cc1cfc00b2550f4f2?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/pangolin2.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/p