e. The reality is climate change will hit the poorest communities in the world. And Philippines is one of the [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Apple Lee","slug":"apple-lee","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/15c705cffb8254909a826b4495da02cc?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/EHVChildren.png","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/EHVChildren-300x200.png 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/EHVChildren.png 451w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoxNzAy","title":"Haze &#8211; who is to blame?","uri":"pm-haze-guest-blog/","slug":"pm-haze-guest-blog","date":"2016-06-30T11:58:49","content":"<p>Can companies clean up our air by cleaning up their palm oil? By Tan Yi Han, PM.HAZE (People&#8217;s Movement Against Haze) When Indonesia’s Minister of Environment and Forestry was reported as telling Singapore to “focus&nbsp;on its own role in addressing the issue instead of making so many comments”, it unsurprisingly led&nbsp;to an explosion of angry [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Deforestation","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/deforestation/","slug":"deforestation"},{"name":"forest fires","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest-fires/","slug":"forest-fires"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/haze/","slug":"haze"},{"name":"Indonesia","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/indonesia/","slug":"indonesia"},{"name":"Palm Oil","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/palm-oil/","slug":"palm-oil"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"},{"name":"Sustainable Consumption","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/sustainable-consumption/","slug":"sustainable-consumption"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/haze-kalimantan.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/haze-kalimantan-300x193.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/haze-kalimantan.jpg 800w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoxNzQ5","title":"Saving Shared Heritage: The Clock Is Ticking&#8230;","uri":"saving-shared-heritage-the-clock-is-ticking/","slug":"saving-shared-heritage-the-clock-is-ticking","date":"2016-06-02T03:50:28","content":"<p>UNESCO WORLD HERITAGE SITES &#8211; RESPECTED OR NEGLECTED? By Vivian Liu What comes to your mind when you think of a UNESCO World Heritage site? The tranquility of Angkor Wat? The breathtaking beauty of the Grand Canyon? Or, for most Singaporeans, it is probably the exquisite design of our very own Botanic Gardens. In fact, [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Vivian Liu","slug":"vivian-liu","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a1893febf756c97a9e663490cd4d463b?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/SCR_53581.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/SCR_53581-300x192.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/SCR_53581-1024x656.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/SCR_53581.jpg 1226w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoxNzQx","title":"4 TIPS TO GREEN YOUR HOLIDAY","uri":"4-tips-green-holiday/","slug":"4-tips-green-holiday","date":"2016-05-27T08:43:39","content":"<p>Singaporeans just love to travel. Our airport is ranked as one of the busiest and best in the world.  So, it comes as no surprise when travel studies show us to be some of the most frequent travelers on the planet. Summer holidays are just around the corner and as you start your vacation planning don&#8217;t [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Vivian Liu","slug":"vivian-liu","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a1893febf756c97a9e663490cd4d463b?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Ocean","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/ocean/","slug":"ocean"},{"name":"Sustainable Consumption","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/sustainable-consumption/","slug":"sustainable-consumption"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Ocean","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/ocean/","slug":"ocean"},{"name":"Sustainable Consumption","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/sustainable-consumption/","slug":"sustainable-con