hange/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-300x113.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-768x288.jpg 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-1024x384.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change.jpg 1600w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyOTY=","title":"Forests: A hot topic at COP21","uri":"forests-a-hot-topic-at-cop21/","slug":"forests-a-hot-topic-at-cop21","date":"2015-12-08T16:37:42","content":"<p>At this year’s UN climate talks in Paris, the spotlight finally shone on an often understated, under-appreciated solution for combating climate change – protecting our forests. Unbeknown to most, deforestation is the second-largest emitter of global CO2 emissions, accounting for nearly 11% of global CO2 emissions. That’s more than the entire transport sector, and only [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"COP21","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cop21/","slug":"cop21"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-300x97.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-768x248.jpg 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-1024x331.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1.jpg 1548w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyNjc=","title":"1 in 6 species at risk of extinction","uri":"1-in-6-species-at-risk-of-extinction/","slug":"1-in-6-species-at-risk-of-extinction","date":"2015-12-04T12:27:50","content":"<p>Move or adapt To survive, plants, animals and birds confronted with climate change have two options: Option one &#8211; ADAPT:  With the speed of climate change we are experiencing already, it’s often not possible for a species to adapt quickly enough to keep up with its changing environment. Option two &#8211; MOVE:  With the amount of habitat [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Orangutan","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/orangutan/","slug":"orangutan"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Wildlife","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/wildlife/","slug":"wildlif